                        1213 PM EST WED JAN 30 2002

       .NOW...THE SHORT TERM FORECAST FOR THE GENESEE VALLEY AND THE
    WESTERN FINGER LAKES REGION.  STEADY SNOW WILL PERSIST SOUTH OF THE
    THRUWAY FROM WYOMING COUNTY ACROSS LIVINGSTON AND ONTARIO COUNTIES.
    ANOTHER INCH OR TWO MAY ACCUMULATE THROUGH 2 PM.  THE SNOW WILL SHOW
    A SOUTHWARD DRIFT.  NOTHING MORE THAN FLURRIES ARE EXPECTED FURTHER
                 NORTH INCLUING THE GREATER ROCHESTER AREA.

